data.enText: having enough ability, experience and knowledge to be able to do sth well

data.chText: 高明的工程师；老练的谈判者；技术熟练的工匠
应付难缠的顾客她很有一手。
data.enText: She is highly skilled at dealing with difficult customers.
a shortage of skilled labour (= people who have had training in a skill)

data.chText: 做家具是技术性很强的活儿。

ex.chText: 我们的主要问题是缺少有技术的人员。
ex.enText: Our main problem is the shortage of skilled personnel.

ex.chText: 他能够熟练地操作计算机。
ex.enText: He is skilled in operating a computer.

synonyms.bx: 通常指人具有足够的能力、经验或知识的，因而能够做好某事。

ex.chText: 我的室友在设计机器人方面是个内行。
ex.enText: My roommate is adept at designing robots.
He is adept at organizational work.

ex.chText: 他是个撒谎高手/熟练的机械师。

synonyms.bx: 指在某一方面具有高超技能的，多用作表语形容词，常后接介词 at/in，但有时也可用作定语。

ex.chText: 詹姆斯对设计车床很在行。
ex.enText: James is expert in designing lathes.
He is expert at playing bridge.

ex.chText: 看来他们对付此类事情非常在行。
ex.enText: They seemed expert in such matters.

synonyms.bx: 指具有专门知识或技能的，强调在某方面经验丰富或特别在行，常后接介词 at/in。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：熟练的，擅长的

tr: having or showing or requiring special skill
example: only the most skilled gymnasts make an Olympic team
a skilled surgeon has many years of training and experience
a skilled reconstruction of her damaged elbow

value.def: Someone who is skilled has the knowledge and ability to do something well.

example.ex: Not all doctors are skilled in helping their patients make choices.
example.tran: 并非所有医生都善于帮助病人作出正确选择。

example.ex: ...a network of amateur but highly skilled observers of wildlife.
example.tran: 由一批知识丰富的业余野生动植物观察者组成的网络

value.tran: 有技术的;有技能的;熟练的

value.def: Skilled work can only be done by people who have had some training.

example.ex: New industries demanded skilled labour not available locally.
example.tran: 新行业所需的技术工人在当地是找不到的。

example.ex: ...skilled workers, such as plumbers and electricians.
example.tran: 管道工和电工等技术工人

value.tran: 需要熟练技术的;需要专门技能的
